It's time to give the bedroom a thorough renovation. This is the last room in the house that only does simple decoration.
Remove the ugly electric heater and brick hearth. Seal the chimney, replace the damaged plaster, repaint. Custom-make a closet.
We usually draw a rough pencil sketch first……
The chaotic phase is over.
Several dead birds were found behind the chimney, their bodies were dried up :(
Preparing for the plastering work next week.
Satisfied with the small niche next to it.
We've put the new closet here (we haven't even started designing yet).
Ha ha, look what we found behind the radiator!
Still remember the small ventilation openings that were added, to prevent the chimney from dampness.
The chimney caps and crowns are all installed. Those crows who like to nest in the chimneys should be safer now.
The plasterer has finished the job. We'll lay the floor tomorrow!
The rubber mat has been laid out completely, and a sanitary paper roller was used to make a part for the vacuum cleaner, used to suck up sawdust.
Some of the flooring has been organized, and we can start laying it now. Let's have a cup of tea and take a break first.
"Ah, the progress is a bit slow today because we need to cut around the frame to match the flooring, which is being installed in the hallway too. It's quite a difficult operation. @user45, you've been complaining about me the whole time."
It's finally done, but everything is all over the place! And to make matters worse, the instruction manual that came with the new bed was completely useless. Tonight I can finally get a good night's sleep!
There is still the corridor floor and baseboards that haven't been done yet. The construction workers didn't come until a month later, so we can only make do and live here for now, with the bare plasterboards in the room.
In the evening, I made a simple DIY, using a chisel and a mallet to cut out a portion of the base of the door frame, so that the floor can be perfectly laid down.
The soft flooring in the corridor has been laid.
Yesterday, we finished laying the floor in the hallway! This morning, we got up at 5 am and went to Heathrow Airport to pick up the package, then took a nap and now we can finally start putting down the skirting board for the hallway. After the glue is dry, we can fill the gaps.
